    <h1 class="article-title">Festivals of India!</h1>
    <p>The fairs and festivals either celebrate the change of seasons or are of a religious nature. For instance, Mewar festival and Holi are celebrated to mark the arrival of the spring season. Teej of Rajasthan marks the onset of the monsoon. On the other hand, Onam in Kerala and Bihu in Assam are celebrated to mark the harvesting season. Other festivals, like the Konark Dance Festival, promote the culture of India. </p>
